  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0da9\u0dd4 \u0dc3\u0dc4 \u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2 21\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc3\u0db8\u0d9c \u0d9a\u0dad\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db8\u0dcf\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0dd4",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Katak caught with powder and 21 lakhs",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Police Special Task Force said that a woman who is said to be the mistress of an alleged organized crime gang member and drug trafficker, 'Dubai Nipuna', was arrested with 20 grams of heroin and over 21 lakh rupees in cash.",
        "The Special Task Force further mentioned that the money in her possession was 2,150,000 rupees and a mobile phone was also seized and handed over to the Police Narcotics Bureau for further investigations.",
        "According to the orders and instructions of Special Task Force Commanding Officer Mr. Varuna Jayasundara, Senior Superintendent of Police P. J. According to the information received by the officers of the Special Task Force Gonahena Camp under the supervision of Mr. Sylvester Wijesinghe, the Station Commander Special Operations Police Inspector SDPN. The Special Task Force said that a team including Mr. Deshapriya arrested the women at the Papiliana Junction in Boralasgamuwa Police Domain, where a 33-year-old resident of Wellawatta area who was in possession of 20 grams of heroin was arrested after a great effort."
      ],
